(Photo: Mickey Welsh/Advertiser file) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
All three of the Week 9 All-Metro Players of the Week have two things in common: They all led their teams to victory, and they all ran for a touchdown. Here’s who made the list this week. 
CLASS 5A-7A 
Akeem Dudley, RB, Sr., Park Crossing 
Dudley ran 10 times for 105 yards and two touchdowns in the Thunderbirds’ 55-12 victory over Russell County. It was his third straight game with 100 yards and a touchdown. 
Park Crossing (8-1) travels to Stanhope Elmore on Friday. 
CLASS 1A-4A 
Nelson Whyte, RB, Sr., Montgomery Academy 
Whyte ran 13 times for 263 yards and five touchdowns in the Eagles’ 65-24 win over Central-Coosa. It was his third game of the year eclipsing 100 yards. 
Montgomery Academy (7-1) travels to Prattville Christian on Friday. 
AISA 
Rashad Walker, QB, So., Macon-East 
Walker completed 6 of 8 passes for 123 yards and three touchdowns in the Knights’ 35-20 victory over Lakeside. He also ran 13 times for 81 yards and a touchdown. 
Macon-East (3-5) hosts Lowndes on Friday. Read or Share this story: http://on.mgmadv.com/1LEPirm TOP VIDEOS
